The paper deals with the study and mitigation of nonlinear interference in WDM systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the optimization of symbol rates and the computation of achievable information rates, which are topics related to optimization (cs.OH) and performance analysis (cs.PF). Finally, the paper considers the impact of polarization on the system performance, which is a topic related to signal processing (cs.SI).
